Guide to getting started with ggplot2 in R

ggplot2 is a data visualization package for the statistical programming language R. Created by Hadley Wickham in 2005, ggplot2 is an implementation of Leland Wilkinsons Grammar of Graphicsa general scheme for data visualization which breaks up graphs into semantic components such as scales and layers. ggplot2 can serve as a replacement for the base graphics in R and contains a number of defaults for web and print display of common scales. Since 2005, ggplot2 has grown in use to become one of the most popular R packages

Allows combination of aesthetics (color,shape, size) with geometric shapes (line, points). Also includes facets for conditional plots, stats for statistical transformations like binning,quantiles & smoothing, Scales fo aesthetics map and Coordinate system

library(ggplot2)
str(mpg)

qplot(displ,hwy,data=mpg,xlab="Displacement",ylab="Highway miles",
      geom=c("point","smooth"))

Lets draw histogram

qplot(hwy,data=mpg,fill=drv)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

###Facets

qplot(displ,hwy,data=mpg,facets=.~drv,geom=c("point","smooth"))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

#rows vs column representation is seprated by ~ character

achieve same thing with

qplot(displ,hwy,data=mpg,facets=.~drv) + geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Can also use Facets with histogram

qplot(hwy,data=mpg,facets=drv~.,binwidth=2)

qplot(log(Petal.Width),data=iris)
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

qplot(log(Petal.Width),data=iris,geom="density")

qplot(log(Petal.Width),data=iris,geom="density",color=Species)

qplot(Petal.Width,Petal.Length,data=iris,color=Species,geom=c("point","smooth"),method="lm")
## Warning: Ignoring unknown parameters: method

##using ggplot

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length,color=Species)) + geom_point()

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm")

flipping coordinates

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm") +
  coord_flip()

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length,color=Species)) + 
  geom_point(size=2,alpha=0.5) +
  facet_grid(.~Species) +
  geom_smooth(method="lm",size=2)

g <- ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) 
g +  geom_point(size=2,alpha=0.5,aes(color=Species)) +
  facet_grid(.~Species) +
  geom_smooth(method="lm",size=2,linetype=2) +
  labs(x="Petal Width",y="Petal Height")

g <- ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Sepal.Length))
g + geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(.~Species) + 
  geom_smooth() +
  theme_bw(base_family="Avenir",base_size=10) +
  labs(x="Petal Width") +
  labs(y="Sepal Length") +
  labs(title="Iris Dataset Petal X Sepal observations")

Bar plot

ggplot(iris,aes(x=Petal.Length,fill=Species)) + geom_bar()

saving plot

png("barplot.png",750,750)
ggplot(iris,aes(x=Petal.Length,fill=Species)) + geom_bar()

Similarly, use tiff(),jpeg(),pdf() functions for exporting the plots

Arrange plots in grid

plot1 <- ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()

plot2 <- ggplot(iris,aes(Sepal.Width,Sepal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()
library(gridExtra)
## Warning: package 'gridExtra' was built under R version 3.6.1
grid.arrange(plot1,plot2,nrow=2)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

apply theme

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() + theme_light()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

custom color themes

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() +  theme(
  panel.background = element_rect(fill = "lightcyan",
                                colour = "lightcyan",
                                size = 1, linetype = "solid"))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

remove grids

ggplot(iris,aes(Petal.Width,Petal.Length)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() +  theme(
  panel.background = element_rect(fill = "lightcyan",
                                colour = "lightcyan",
                                size = 1, linetype = "solid"),
  panel.grid.major =    element_blank(),
  panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
  axis.line = element_line(size = 0.5, linetype = "solid",
                                   colour = "black"))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

boxplot

ggplot(iris, aes(Species,Petal.Length)) + geom_boxplot(aes(fill = Species))
